    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @vittominacori \r\n\r\nAFAIK, the reason we do\r\n```solidity\r\nif (initialOwner == address(0)) {\r\n    revert OwnableInvalidOwner(address(0));\r\n}\r\n```\r\ninstead of \r\n```solidity\r\nif (initialOwner == address(0)) {\r\n    revert OwnableInvalidOwner(initialOwner);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nis because the first one is cheaper. At least it used to be, and I'm guessing `PUSH0` is re-enforcing that. Sure it should be the same ... but the truth is how you get the 0 value actually as an impact.\r\n",
